# Enhanced Web UI with Interactive Power Graphs

## Overview

Added a new interactive real-time power monitoring graph to the PSU-5000 web interface. Users can now visualize voltage, current, and power over time with zoom, pan, and data export capabilities.

![New Power Graph Interface]({{ files.find(f => f.path && f.path.includes('screenshot')).cdnUrl }})

## Features

### Real-Time Graphing
- **Live updates**: Graph refreshes every 100ms with new data points
- **Multiple traces**: Voltage (V), Current (A), and Power (W) on same graph
- **Color-coded**: Voltage=Blue, Current=Red, Power=Green
- **Auto-scaling**: Y-axis automatically adjusts to data range

### Interactive Controls

![Feature Demonstration]({{ files.find(f => f.path && f.path.includes('demo.gif')).cdnUrl }})

Users can interact with the graph using:

- **Zoom**: Scroll wheel or pinch gesture to zoom in/out on time axis
- **Pan**: Click and drag to scroll through historical data
- **Trace toggle**: Click legend to show/hide individual traces
- **Cursor readout**: Hover over graph to see exact values at any point
- **Time range selector**: Quick presets (1min, 5min, 1hr, 24hr)

### Data Export
- **CSV export**: Download graph data as comma-separated values
- **Screenshot**: Capture current graph view as PNG image
- **Date range selection**: Export specific time periods
- **Custom sampling**: Choose data resolution (1/sec to 1/min)

## Technical Implementation

**Technology Stack:**
- Frontend: Chart.js 4.4.0 (see [library documentation]({{ files.find(f => f.description.includes('Chart.js')).url }}))
- WebSocket for real-time data streaming
- IndexedDB for client-side data caching (up to 24hrs)
- Responsive design (works on mobile/tablet)

**Performance:**
- Renders 60fps even with 1000+ data points
- Minimal CPU impact (<2% on modern browsers)
- Memory-efficient rolling buffer (auto-purges old data)

## User Interface Improvements

The new graph interface represents a significant improvement over the previous static display:

![Before/After Comparison]({{ files.find(f => f.description.includes('comparison')).cdnUrl }})

**Before:**
- Simple numeric readouts only
- No historical data visibility
- No trend analysis capability

**After:**
- Full interactive graphing with history
- Visual trend identification
- Zoom/pan for detailed analysis
- Data export for logging/analysis

## Use Cases

### Battery Charging Monitoring
Users can visualize the complete charge cycle:
1. Constant current phase (current flat, voltage rising)
2. Constant voltage phase (voltage flat, current declining)
3. Charge complete (current drops to minimum)

### Load Testing
Observe device behavior under varying loads:
- Identify current spikes during device startup
- Monitor steady-state power consumption
- Detect intermittent load variations

### Power Supply Verification
Verify PSU performance and calibration:
- Check voltage/current regulation quality
- Identify noise or oscillations
- Verify transient response

## Configuration

Graph settings can be customized in the web interface settings panel:

```javascript
// Example configuration (accessible via settings)
{
  updateInterval: 100,        // ms between updates
  maxDataPoints: 10000,       // maximum points to display
  defaultTimeRange: 300,      // seconds (5 minutes)
  enableDataCaching: true,    // cache data in IndexedDB
  traces: {
    voltage: { enabled: true, color: '#0066cc' },
    current: { enabled: true, color: '#cc0000' },
    power: { enabled: true, color: '#00cc66' }
  }
}
```

## Browser Compatibility

Tested and supported on:
- ✓ Chrome 120+ (desktop & mobile)
- ✓ Firefox 121+
- ✓ Safari 17+
- ✓ Edge 120+

**Minimum requirements:**
- WebSocket support
- HTML5 Canvas
- ES6 JavaScript
- 1024x768 minimum resolution (responsive down to 320px width)

## Accessibility

The graph interface includes accessibility features:

- **Keyboard navigation**: Tab through controls, arrow keys to navigate data
- **Screen reader support**: ARIA labels and live regions for data updates
- **High contrast mode**: Respects system high contrast settings
- **Configurable colors**: Users can customize trace colors for color blindness
- **Data table view**: Alternative non-graphical view of same data

